description: Rachel Reeves said the UK will invest billions of pounds boosting childcare services and rebuilding schools as part of her crucial first budget on Wednesday.
title: UK to Invest Over £3 Billion in Childcare and Rebuilding Schools

description: Japan looks set for one of its closest national elections in years as voters go to the polls Sunday to decide whether to keep the scandal-tainted Liberal Democratic Party in power.
title: Japan Set for Closest Vote in Years as LDP Vies to Stay in Power

description: Queensland became Australia’s first mainland state to elect a center-right government in more than 18 months, breaking the Labor Party’s hold on power ahead of a national election due by May.
title: Australia’s Center-Right Wins Queensland Election, Breaks Trend

description: Donald Trump and Kamala Harris are blitzing through the “Blue Wall” states that are expected to determine the outcome of the US election, betting on high-profile events over the weekend to help drive voters to the polls on Nov. 5.
title: Trump Pitches Detroit Renaissance While Biden Courts Labor Vote

description: European Central Bank Governing Council member Klaas Knot urged European governments to get their finances in order — highlighting France’s particular need to do so.
title: France and Europe Need to Get Finances in Order, ECB’s Knot Says

description: Demonstrators gathered for a march in central Lisbon on Saturday to commemorate a man shot by police earlier in the week, a death that led to acts of violence and focused attention on the poorer suburbs of the Portuguese capital.
title: Demonstrators in Lisbon March to Commemorate Man Shot by Police

description: The risk of a wider, unpredictable regional war remains high, if averted for now.
title: Israel’s Strike on Iran Was Smart. Now Take the Win.

description: Montenegro’s ambition to become a member of the European Union by 2028 is “reachable,” European Commission President Ursula von der Leyen said on Saturday.
title: Montenegro’s 2028 EU Entry Goal Is Reachable, Von Der Leyen Says

description: Voters in Uruguay are set to cast their ballots Sunday in a presidential race that’s being overshadowed by a contentious pension overhaul.
title: Uruguay Goes to Polls With Investors Wary of Pension Overhaul

description: Ireland’s central bank chief cautioned against only focusing on Europe’s problems, saying it’s still the most livable part of the world.
title: Europe Still Best Place to Live, Irish Central Bank Chief Says

description: Russian demands in the Group of 20 that countries need to cooperate are a mockery given its invasion of Ukraine in 2022, Bundesbank President Joachim Nagel said, blaming part of Germany’s economic troubles on the war.
title: Bundesbank Chief Is Mad at Russia’s Calls for Global Cooperation

description: Ex-Trade Minister Jean-Louis Billon said he will seek the Democratic Party of Ivory Coast’s support to be its presidential candidate in next year’s elections.
title: Ivory Coast Ex-Trade Minister Challenges Thiam’s Presidential Bid

description: Zimbabwe President Emmerson Mnangagwa declined an offer by the ruling party to extend his term of office by two years until 2030.
title: Zimbabwe Leader Declines Ruling Party’s Offer to Stay Until 2030

description: Donald Trump and Vice President Kamala Harris are tied with 49% support each among likely voters just days before the US presidential election, according to a new national survey conducted by Emerson College.
title: Trump, Harris Tied With 49% Each in New National Emerson Poll

description: Israel’s assault on Iran early Saturday, coordinated with Washington and limited to missile and air defense sites, was more restrained than many expected and may help diplomatic efforts to return hostages and limit the combat in both Lebanon and Gaza.
title: Israel’s Limited Attack on Iran May Help Foster a Regional Deal

description: Senegal’s program with the International Monetary Fund needs to be reworked after an audit showed higher debt and budget deficit than previously reported.
title: Senegal to Revise IMF Program After Audit Shows Higher Deficit

description: The UK agreed to hold talks about its historical involvement in the slave trade in a joint statement with other Commonwealth leaders in Samoa, but continued to rule out the prospect of financial reparations.
title: UK Agrees to Hold Talks With Commonwealth on Its Slavery Legacy

description: KYIV, Ukraine (AP) — A Russian drone strike killed a teenager in Kyiv during a nighttime barrage on the Ukrainian capital that lasted for hours, officials said, while four people were reportedly killed in a missile attack on central Ukraine that also left at least 20 injured.
title: Russian Strikes on Kyiv, Central Ukraine Kill Four People and Injure Dozens

description: Thailand plans to lift the retirement age for both the private and government sectors to 65, due to improvements in healthcare and medical technology, the Bangkok Post reported.
title: Thailand Will Raise Retirement Age to 65, Bangkok Post Reports

description: The UK is set to announce a change to the Universal Credit program that limits the amount which can be cut from benefits to repay short-term loans and debts, the Guardian reported, citing an unidentified source in government.
title: UK to Reduce Benefit Cuts for Indebted Households, Guardian Says

description: The US heavily taxed imports for much of its history before largely abandoning the policy, beginning in the 1930s, as government leaders embraced the idea of free trade. High tariffs made a comeback during the presidency of Donald Trump, who adopted them in an effort to revitalize American manufacturing and to counter what the US regards as China’s unfair trade practices. Trump’s successor Joe Biden kept the trend going.
title: Why Trump’s Plan to Escalate Tariffs Has So Many Haters

description: France’s youngest-ever finance minister is tasked with reining in the country’s runaway public finances amid political uncertainty.
title: As His Plans Unravel, Macron Finds a True Believer for Finance Chief

description: Rachel Reeves drew cheers from investors at a British Embassy reception in Washington this week when she pointed out the budget she’ll deliver on Oct. 30 will be the first by a female Chancellor of the Exchequer in the 800-year history of the role. It will also be a legacy-making moment that shapes British politics for the rest of the decade.
title: Reeves Bets Britain Will Learn to Love Decade-Defining Budget

description: Former President Donald Trump said he’d consider entirely replacing income taxes with tariffs, conceded he had botched senior staff appointments, and teased a possible revelation about extraterrestrial life during a freewheeling three-hour podcast with comedian Joe Rogan on Friday.
title: Trump Talks Xi, Tariffs and Aliens in Freewheeling Rogan Podcast

description: China’s anti-graft agency punished 589,000 people in first nine months of the year for discipline violations, including accepting or offering bribery.
title: China Punished 589,000 People for Graft in Nine Months

description: Kamala Harris tethered ex-President Donald Trump to the rollback of federal abortion rights in a Friday night rally headlined by celebrity singer  Beyoncé Knowles-Carter as the vice president sought to elevate her standing with female voters in the final days before the election.
title: Harris Taps Beyoncé’s Star Power to Press Case Against Trump

description: China’s recent rollout of stimulus is centered around lifting domestic demand and hitting the nation’s annual growth goal, said Vice Finance Minister Liao Min, as investors await a meeting of lawmakers expected to unveil details of Beijing’s crucial fiscal package.
title: China’s Stimulus Aims to Boost Consumption, Top Official Says

description: Israel said its military “completed precise and targeted strikes against military targets in a number of areas in Iran,” adding that its warplanes returned to their bases.
title: Israel Says Airstrikes Against Iran’s Military Targets Completed

description: US intelligence officials say Russian operatives attempting to interfere with the American election were behind a fake video supposedly showing someone tearing up ballots in Pennsylvania.
title: US Says Russians Made Fake Video of Ballots Being Destroyed

description: The death toll in the Philippines from Severe Tropical Storm Trami rose to at least 70, and the Southeast Asian nation is bracing for a new cyclone and Trami’s possible return.
title: Philippines’ Deaths From Trami Rises to 70 as Storm Risks Return
